# Architecture

Full design lives in [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md).

Implementation is **mandatory in three phases**: **A → B → C** (all part of the project, not optional demos).

## Phase overview

| Phase | Focus | Key tech |
|-------|-------|----------|
| **A** | Document core + CLI end-to-end | Tesseract, Qwen vision, Python layout/table (gRPC), enricher, markdown |
| **B** | Platform async | PostgreSQL, MinIO, RabbitMQ, Redis, REST, WebSocket, JWT, docker-compose |
| **C** | Production | K8s+HPA, Kafka, Prometheus/Grafana, Loki, OTel/Jaeger, CI/CD, retry/DLQ |

## Hybrid OCR (scan/image pages)

1. **Pass 1 — Tesseract** (offline) → draft text
2. **Pass 2 — Qwen vision** (image + draft) → refined Markdown
3. **Fallback** to Tesseract if Qwen fails

Digital PDFs with text layer use `extractor` directly.

A1 detector scans the text layer of ALL pages and classifies the file as
`AllDigital` / `AllScan` / `Mixed`. Uniform files take a fast path (extract OR OCR for
the whole file); only `Mixed` files use per-page routing (digital page -> extractor,
scan page -> hybrid OCR), merged back in page order.

## Layering (delivery -> usecase -> domain)

- `internal/domain` — entities + ports
- `internal/usecase` — upload / process / build
- `internal/core` — detector, extractor, ocr, enricher, markdown, converter
- `internal/adapter` — postgres, minio, rabbitmq, redis, kafka, llm, layout/table gRPC clients
- `internal/delivery` — http, ws, grpc
- `pkg/document` — shared model

## Pipeline

```
detector -> extractor (digital) | hybrid OCR (scan)
  -> layout gRPC -> table gRPC -> enricher -> markdown -> .md + assets
```

## Rules

- Wire dependencies in `cmd/*/main.go`; domain must not import adapter/delivery.
- New formats: add `Extractor`. New OCR backends: implement `ocr.Engine`.
- Keep `internal/core` transport-agnostic (CLI, api, worker share the same core).
